* Installing Git

.link https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Getting-Started-Installing-Git Git-SCM Install Docs

.link https://git-scm.com/download/linux *Linux*(Fedora*based)*

    sudo yum install git-all
    sudo dnf install git-all

.link https://git-scm.com/download/linux *Linux*(Debian*based)*

    sudo apt-get install git-all

.link https://git-scm.com/download/mac *Mac*

    brew install git-all

.link https://git-scm.com/download/windows *Windows*

Must use installer from link

* Configure Git

- Change Git Name
    git config --global user.name "Will Dixon"
- Change Email
    git config --global user.email "dixonwille@hotmail.com"

* What is Github?

- Online git repository
- Specifiy permissions for repository
- Create Tasks and Issues
- Pull Request/Code Review

* Create an account

* Create SSH Keys

These keys are used so that git know that you are who you say you are.

    ssh-keygen -t rsa

Press enter for all values for defaults.

* Add keys to Github

In `$HOME/.ssh` there is an `id_rsa.pub` file.

- Copy the contents
- Goto Github Settings
- Goto _SSH_and_GPG_Keys_
.link https://github.com/settings/keys
- Click _New_SSH_Key_
- Give it a meaningful name
- Paste the contents

* Test keys

    ssh git@github.com

Should state your name and that you are authenticated correctly, but github does not have an SSH socket.

